<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,626]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Arms of postgonite slightly longer than anterior proccesses. Cercus short, subtriangular, pale brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1337,1436,151,177]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Female.</emphasis>
Body length: 3.0– 
<quantity box="[372,468,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. Wing: 
<number box="[563,654,189,215]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="3.0" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.9">2.9–3.1</number>
long, 
<quantity box="[732,878,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.2 mm</quantity>
wide. Very similar to males, except as noted. Frons as wide as face, metallic green with some bluish reflections, covered by silvery pruinosity; clypeal suture evident; 
<number box="[334,349,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of strong proclinate vt; palpus blackish. Legs. I: 
<number box="[989,1028,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.8">1.8</number>
, 
<number box="[1041,1080,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.9">1.9</number>
, 1.0, 
<number box="[1146,1185,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.5">0.5</number>
, 
<number box="[1198,1238,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.3">0.3</number>
, 
<number box="[1251,1291,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.2">0.2</number>
, 
<number box="[1304,1344,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.1">0.1</number>
. II: 
<number box="[1392,1432,264,290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="2.2">2.2</number>
, 
<number box="[151,191,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="2.4">2.4</number>
, 
<number box="[204,244,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.4">1.4</number>
, 
<number box="[256,296,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number box="[309,349,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.4">0.4</number>
, 
<number box="[362,402,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.3">0.3</number>
, 
<number box="[415,456,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.2">0.2</number>
. III: 
<number box="[514,554,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="2.5">2.5</number>
, 
<number box="[567,607,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="2.5">2.5</number>
, 
<number box="[619,659,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.9">0.9</number>
, 
<number box="[672,712,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number box="[725,765,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.4">0.4</number>
, 
<number box="[778,818,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.2">0.2</number>
, 
<number box="[831,872,301,327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="0.2">0.2</number>
. Femora without conspicuous row of setae. TII with 
<number box="[210,225,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
large ad at base, and 
<number box="[473,488,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
pd and 
<number box="[580,594,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
ventral seta shorter near middle; 
<collectionCode box="[983,1030,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">TIII</collectionCode>
with 
<number box="[1096,1111,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
ad on basal half and 
<number box="[1356,1400,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
pd along length. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[319,461,375,401]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[479,629,376,402]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,197,1392]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[172,1416,197,1403]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrysotus spectabilis (Loew), specimen from Dominica, B. W. I., female oviscapt (13, 15 dorsal view; 14, right lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196240/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Figs. 
<number box="[549,629,376,402]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin of Tg 
<number box="[925,970,376,402]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
with deep inverted U-shaped incision (
<figureCitation box="[160,253,413,439]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,197,1392]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[172,1416,197,1403]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrysotus spectabilis (Loew), specimen from Dominica, B. W. I., female oviscapt (13, 15 dorsal view; 14, right lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196240/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Fig. 
<number box="[219,253,413,439]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tg 
<number box="[311,324,413,439]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
and St 
<number box="[413,426,413,439]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
divided into two rod-like sclerites, St 
<number box="[896,909,413,439]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="8.0">8</number>
sclerites connected mesally by sclerotized bridge; dorsal surface of acantophorites (Tg 
<number box="[666,695,450,476]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="10.0">10</number>
) with crest of 
<number box="[864,879,450,476]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="5.0">5</number>
rhomboid spines and 
<number box="[1138,1152,450,476]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
lateral seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,626]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,339,487,513]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">Comments.</emphasis>
As also noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Aldrich" box="[547,723,488,514]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" refString="Aldrich, J. M. (1901) Supplement. Dolichopodidae. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.) Biologia Centrali-Americana. London, pp. 333 - 366, pl. 6, figs. 7 - 24." type="journal article" year="1901">
Aldrich (
<number box="[652,715,488,514]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1901.0">1901</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, in the material of 
<taxonomicName box="[941,1100,488,513]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spectabilis">
<emphasis box="[941,1100,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">C. spectabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
studied here the eyes are not always fully holoptic, a condition seen in the illustration by 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson" box="[906,1397,525,551]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" refString="Robinson, H. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R. (1981) Dolichopodidae. In: McAlpine, J. F., Peterson, B. V., Shewell, G. E., Teskey, H. J., Vockeroth, J. R. &amp; Wood, D. M. (Co-ords.) Manual of Nearctic Diptera, Vol. 1. Agriculture Canada Monograph, 27, pp. 265 - 639." type="journal article" year="1981">
Robinson and Vockeroth (
<number box="[1230,1297,525,551]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="1981.0">1981</number>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1310,1386,525,551]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="6.[151,278,1941,1965]" captionTargetBox="[382,1199,194,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[382,1200,194,1923]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Chrysotus maculatus (Parent) comb. nov. (= Diaphorus maculipennis Robinson). 5 – 6. Male hypopygium, specimen from Nova Granada (5, ventral view; 6, left lateral view). 7 – 8. Female oviscapt, specimen from Nova Xavantina (7, dorsal view; 8, right lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196237/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="60">
Fig. 
<number box="[1368,1386,525,551]" pageId="11" pageNumber="60" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
)
